Package ohos.data.distributed.user

Interface SingleKvStore

  • All Superinterfaces:
    KvStore

    public interface SingleKvStore
extends KvStore
    Provides methods related to single-version distributed databases.

    To create a SingleKvStore database, you can use the KvManager.getKvStoreâ€‹(Options, String) method with KvStoreType set to SINGLE_VERSION for the input parameter Options. This database synchronizes data to other databases in time sequence. The SingleKvStore database does not support synchronous transactions, or data search using snapshots.

    Since:
    1
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Data#DATA_DISTRIBUTEDDATAMGR

      • getResultSet

        KvStoreResultSet getResultSet​(String keyPrefix)
                       throws KvStoreException
        Obtains the result sets with a specified prefix from a KvStore database. The KvStoreResultSet object can be used to query all key-value pairs that meet the search criteria. Each KvStore instance can have a maximum of four KvStoreResultSet objects at the same time. If you have created four objects, calling this method will return a failure. Therefore, you are advised to call the closeResultSet method to close unnecessary KvStoreResultSet objects in a timely manner.
        Parameters:
        keyPrefix - Indicates the key prefix to match.
        Returns:
        Returns the KvStoreResultSet objects.
        Throws:
        KvStoreException - Throws this exception if any of the following errors occurs: INVALID_ARGUMENT, SERVER_UNAVAILABLE, IPC_ERROR, and DB_ERROR.
        Since:
        1

      • sync

        void sync​(List<String> deviceIdList,
          SyncMode mode)
   throws KvStoreException
        Synchronizes SingleKvStore databases.

        This method returns immediately and sync result will be returned through asynchronous callback.

        Parameters:
        deviceIdList - Indicates the list of IDs of devices whose SingleKvStore databases are to be synchronized.
        mode - Indicates the synchronization mode, PUSH, PULL, or PUSH_PULL.
        Throws:
        KvStoreException - Throws this exception if no SingleKvStore database is available.
        Since:
        1

      • sync

        void sync​(List<String> deviceIdList,
          SyncMode mode,
          int allowedDelayMs)
   throws KvStoreException
        Synchronizes the database to the specified devices with the specified delay allowed.
        Parameters:
        deviceIdList - Indicates the list of devices to which to synchronize the database.
        mode - Indicates the synchronization mode. The value can be PUSH, PULL, or PUSH_PULL.
        allowedDelayMs - Indicates the delay allowed for the synchronization, in milliseconds.
        Throws:
        KvStoreException - Throws this exception if any of the following errors occurs: INVALID_ARGUMENT, SERVER_UNAVAILABLE, IPC_ERROR, and DB_ERROR.
        Since:
        3
